Our team is using two Kraken x60 motors to drive our TTB 2 stage elevator. However, when trying to test the elevator, we noticed that our motors weren’t running at all. We tried code that only ran those motors and did nothing else, but the motors weren’t spinning at all and the status lights weren’t changing. We then tried running one of the motors with Phoenix Tuner, but the motor did not move whatsoever despite Phoenix Tuner stating that it was enabled.

We have double checked that our motors have the correct IDs and firmware in Phoenix Tuner. Both of the motors are on a CANivore. We have cut down our Krakens’ motor shafts to work with the short block configuration for sport gearboxes, but we were very careful during this and aren’t sure how it could have damaged the motor internally. We’re pretty lost on where to go from here other than just using a new motor, so any help would be greatly appreciated.

Here’s our robot code if it helps: github
